*********************CS653 "Huffman Encoding/Decoding"*******************
***************************Project Readme*********************************
To install (this will generate binary in /home/bin/)

	$cabal install --prefix=$HOME â€“user
 or
 	$runhaskell Setup configure --user --prefix=$HOME
	$runhaskell Setup build
	$runhaskell Setup install

then use as:
>for encoding:
	$huffmanencode test

this will generate the compressed test.cmp file and one test.key file which is used while decoding

>foe decoding:
	$huffmandecode test.cmp test.key foo

this will decode the test.cmp file using the test.key provided and put the result in foo


this project has a darcs repository at patch-tag.com
to get the patch:
	$darcs get http://patch-tag.com/r/svimal/huffman_coding

